  "prompt": "I got placed in TCS's EIS stream in my campus placement. Will I get a job in EIS or in IT?",
  "response": "Congratulations on your placement! Typically, when you are placed in a specific stream during campus placements, it indicates the area in which you will initially start your career. In your case, being placed in TCS's EIS (Engineering and Industrial Services) stream suggests that you will begin your job related to EIS, not the generic IT sector.\n\nEIS in TCS involves domains like engineering services, product lifecycle management, and other industrial services. However, it's worth noting that roles and projects can evolve over time, and there might be opportunities for lateral movement to different streams, including IT, based on your performance, skills, and career goals.\n\nTo be certain, you could also reach out to your TCS onboarding coordinator or HR representative for more specific details regarding your placement and future job assignments.",
